article.headline: Georgia St 77, James Madison 53
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Malcolm Manier scored a career-high 27 points, 17 in the second half, to lead Georgia State to a 77-53 win over James Madison on Thursday night. The Panthers (6-14, 3-9 Colonial Athletic Association) went into halftime leading 29-25 over the Dukes (3-16, 0-11). Rashad Chase scored two free throws, putting Georgia State up 60-38 with 7:30 to play and capping off a 20-3 scoring run. Georgia State took its largest lead on a layup by Justin Billingslea that put the team up 76-49 with 1:09 left. Herman Favors added 18 for the Panthers, and Billingslea had 10. Chris Cathlin led James Madison with 11 points and nine rebounds, and Jomo Belfor added 10. The Dukes were kept to 31.5 percent shooting, and Georgia State went 44 percent from the field.
